text: U.S. Route 69 (US 69) is a major north-south United States highway. When it was first created, it was only long. It has been expanded into a Minnesota to Texas cross-country route. The highway's southern endpoint (as well as those of US 287 and US 96) is in Port Arthur, Texas at an intersection with State Highway 87. Its northern endpoint is in Albert Lea, Minnesota at Minnesota State Highway 13. ==References== ==Other websites== * Endpoints of U.S. Highway 69 Category:U.S. Highways
title: U.S. Route 69
